{
  "texts": [
    "• Questionable agreement between automatic metrics and human judgment.",
    "Some investigations have revealed the discrepancies between the coherence metrics and human evaluation: they find that automatic metrics declare winner models when the corresponding human evaluation does not.",
    "This raises concerns that coherence metrics, originally designed for older models, possibly are incompatible with the newer neural topic models (Doogan and Buntine 2021; Hoyle et al 2021).",
    "We believe similar concerns may extend to diversity metrics: they may also be inconsistent with human assessments.",
    "We detail the reasons and offer a heuristic solution in Sect. 6."
  ]
}